page.title: 18A Typical day in Manuden 1
page.content: It was midnight on Monday. It was very quiet because nearly everybody was asleep. Some people were just going to bed. A few cars were going by. At one o'clock it was even quieter because now apart from a few people everyone was asleep. There are no birds. There are no lights on now.Between three and four o'clock the birds start to wake up but it is still quite peaceful. At five o'clock some dads that have a long way to drive to work are getting up now. Nearly all the birds were singing. Between six and seven the milkman starts his rounds. Now lots more people are getting up. At eight o'clock everybody is awake. Children are now on their way to school either by coach, car or walking. Dads are going to work. At nine o'clock all the children are going inside to start their work.
